#   SUBS-015: `blob:<path>` without `?ref` returns KEEPNONE in the parent

**LOW (found mid-fix in [SUBS-011]/[SUBS-012]).**  `be blob:<path>` with **no**
`?ref` slot returns `KEEPNONE` even on a plain parent file (not submodule-
related).  Per VERBS.md §"Open edges", `blob:file.c` (no ref) is defined as the
git-hash-object bytes of the wt's on-disk file, and `blob:file.c?` (empty ref)
as the tracked-blob via sniff's index — but the no-ref form resolves to nothing.

##  Repro
 -  `be blob:main.c?master` → bytes (works).
 -  `be blob:main.c` (no `?ref`) → KEEPNONE.

##  Expected
`blob:<path>` (no ref) yields the wt on-disk bytes (git-hash-object semantics);
`blob:<path>?` (empty ref) yields the tracked-blob bytes.

##  Notes
Surfaced while building projector sub-recursion (SUBS-011/012); the sub-shard
routing is unaffected — this is a pre-existing parent-side gap in `blob:`
ref-resolution.  Filed so it is not lost.

